From: rocm-patches-7.2.1 maintainers
Subject: [PATCH] rocprof-sys 1.3.0: fix SIGSEGV at rocprofiler_configure +0x404

Apply against: ROCm/rocm-systems @ tag rocm-7.2.1
                (= projects/rocprofiler-systems VERSION 1.3.0,
                   the source baseline shipped with ROCm 7.2.0 / 7.2.1).

Bug:
    rocprof-sys-run SIGSEGVs in rocprofiler_configure +0x404 during
    static-init when the target binary is an MPI + OpenMP-target
    offload application. Crash is timing-sensitive (a Heisenbug
    under gdb).

Two functional changes, both inside the lone v1.3.0 implementation
of rocprofiler_configure() in rocprofiler-sdk.cpp. (v1.3.0 inlines
the SDK tool-configuration logic directly into
rocprofiler_configure(); the separate sdk_tool_configure() helper
is a v1.5.0+ refactor.)

  1. Promote the `static bool _first` once-guard to a
     std::atomic<bool> exchange. v1.3.0 already had a non-atomic
     once-guard inside an unnamed-scope block; making it atomic is
     race-safe across the OMPT + rocprofiler-sdk static-init paths
     that can both reach this entry point (the SDK's pthread_once
     wrapper, and the OMPT-driven ompt_start_tool path).

  2. Flip `&&` to `||` in the init-tooling guard:
        if(!settings_are_configured() && state < Active)
            init_tooling()
     becomes
        if(!settings_are_configured() || state < Active)
            init_tooling()
     The original AND short-circuited init_tooling() whenever
     settings_are_configured() was already true (e.g. set by
     rocprof-sys-instrument's static constructor) but state had not
     yet reached Active. The function then proceeded into
     client_data construction and rocprofiler_at_internal_thread_create(),
     touching the timemory settings registry (a std::map<string,
     tim::tsettings*> serialised through cereal::PrettyJsonWriter)
     before the global state machine was Active -- which is the
     std::__throw_bad_optional_access path visible in the crash bt
     (frames 6-10) and the rocprofiler_configure +0x404 SEGV
     (frame 11).

Reference (the same logical fix as it landed on develop in v1.6.0
by way of PR #3412): https://github.com/ROCm/rocm-systems/pull/3412

Files touched: 1 (rocprofiler-sdk.cpp).

---
diff --git a/projects/rocprofiler-systems/source/lib/rocprof-sys/library/rocprofiler-sdk.cpp b/projects/rocprofiler-systems/source/lib/rocprof-sys/library/rocprofiler-sdk.cpp
index ec72a14550..7e837c2d29 100644
--- a/projects/rocprofiler-systems/source/lib/rocprof-sys/library/rocprofiler-sdk.cpp
+++ b/projects/rocprofiler-systems/source/lib/rocprof-sys/library/rocprofiler-sdk.cpp
@@ -2395,18 +2395,21 @@ rocprofiler_configure(uint32_t version, const char* runtime_version, uint32_t pr
                       rocprofiler_client_id_t* id)
 {
     // only activate once
+    // (atomic so the OMPT + rocprofiler-sdk static-init paths cannot
+    // race past the guard and double-enter the body)
     {
-        static bool _first = true;
-        if(!_first) return nullptr;
-        _first = false;
+        static std::atomic<bool> _first{ true };
+        if(!_first.exchange(false)) return nullptr;
     }
 
     if(!tim::get_env("ROCPROFSYS_INIT_TOOLING", true)) return nullptr;
     if(!tim::settings::enabled()) return nullptr;
 
-    if(!rocprofsys::config::settings_are_configured() &&
+    if(!rocprofsys::config::settings_are_configured() ||
        rocprofsys::get_state() < rocprofsys::State::Active)
+    {
         rocprofsys_init_tooling_hidden();
+    }
 
     if(!rocprofsys::config::get_use_rocm())
     {
